    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear offensive anchor; his score of 80.98 is fueled by a massive +19% bump in SP skill facing Roki Sasaki and a favorable +14% platoon edge, making him a high-upside play despite the lower batting order spot. Following him are **Junior Caminero** (71.50) and **Trea Turner** (70.16), both benefiting significantly from top-of-the-order protections and favorable SP matchups. **Kyle Schwarber** (66.62) remains a potent high-floor asset, as his elite 0.402 xwOBA offsets the modest park factors against Bryce Elder. We are also tracking wind conditions closely, as the \"Wind Out\" benefit provides a subtle tailwind for **Hyeseong Kim** and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** to potentially outperform their base projections.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's roster was keeping **Jerar Encarnacion** on the bench at 39.93, agonizingly close to our 40.0 floor. While **Jerar Encarnacion** shows promise, his matchup against Eury P\u00e9rez proved too daunting for the optimizer to justify a start, especially with a negative park factor further depressing his ceiling. Meanwhile, **Victor Scott II** (38.48) remains a high-variance asset due to his elite speed\u2014which we normally overweight\u2014but his unfavorable matchup against Bryan Woo and a bottom-order projection forced him to the pine today. With **Carson Benge** facing a postponement and **Christian Yelich** sidelined on the IL, we are leaning into our current depth, though we will keep a sharp eye on late lineup adjustments for **Dillon Dingler**, **Gary Sanchez**, and **Chase Meidroth** to ensure our batting order assumptions hold up against these confirmed starters.",
